Gov. Adegboyega Oyetola of Osun, has offered his condolences to the lawmaker representing Oyo Central Senatorial District, Sen. Teslim Folarin, over the demise of his wife, Angela, who died on Friday. Oyetola in a statement by his Chief Press Secretary, Ismail Omipidan on Saturday in Osogbo, expressed sadness over her death.   Oyetola, who described the incident as shocking and sad, urged the family especially, the bereaved husband, to accept the incident as the will of Allah. He equally extended his heartfelt condolences to the government and people of Oyo State, particularly the people of Oyo Central Senatorial District and all other persons affected by her death.   “On behalf of my family, government and people of Osun, we  offer our heartfelt condolences to the Teslim Folarin family and share their grief at such a time as this. “May Almighty Allah comfort the entire family, give them the fortitude to bear the loss and accept the soul of the departed,” Oyetola said.(NAN)